<paragraph blockId="18.[151,685,169,1669]" box="[151,251,169,195]" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,685,169,1669]" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">
For many monocyrtid lower Tithonian species from the material we studied in the present paper it is difficult to establish whether they belong to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Wever in De Wever, Sanfilippo, Riedel &amp; Gruber" authorityYear="1979" box="[262,343,299,325]" class="Polycystina" family="Poulpidae" genus="Poulpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nassellaria" pageId="18" pageNumber="23" phylum="Radiozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[262,343,299,325]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">Poulpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pessagno" authorityYear="1977" box="[522,609,298,324]" class="Polycystina" family="Poulpidae" genus="Saitoum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nassellaria" pageId="18" pageNumber="23" phylum="Radiozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[522,609,298,324]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">Saitoum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Some of them have the arches Al rather well marked on the surface and sometimes the arch AV is weakly sketched. In other species of comparable morphology, especially when the cephalic wall is thick, these arches are not visible. As De Wever (
<emphasis box="[160,182,490,515]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">in</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="DE WEVER P. &amp; SANFILIPPO A. &amp; RIEDEL W. R. &amp; GRUBER B." box="[192,437,490,517]" pageId="18" pageNumber="23" pagination="75 - 110" refId="ref34369" refString="DE WEVER P., SANFILIPPO A., RIEDEL W. R. &amp; GRUBER B. 1979. - Triassic radiolarians from Greece, Sicily and Turkey. Micropaleontology 25 (1): 75 - 110." type="journal article" year="1979">
De Wever 
<emphasis box="[315,362,490,517]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">et al</emphasis>
. 1979
</bibRefCitation>
) remarked, the members of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Wever in De Wever, Sanfilippo, Riedel &amp; Gruber" authorityYear="1979" box="[344,425,523,549]" class="Polycystina" family="Poulpidae" genus="Poulpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nassellaria" pageId="18" pageNumber="23" phylum="Radiozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[344,425,523,549]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">Poulpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are superficially similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pessagno" authorityYear="1977" box="[183,338,554,580]" class="Polycystina" family="Poulpidae" genus="Saitoum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nassellaria" pageId="18" pageNumber="23" phylum="Radiozoa" rank="species" species="pagei">
<emphasis box="[183,338,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">Saitoum pagei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[400,448,554,580]" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pessagno" authorityYear="1977" box="[151,243,586,612]" class="Polycystina" family="Poulpidae" genus="Saitoum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nassellaria" pageId="18" pageNumber="23" phylum="Radiozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,243,586,612]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">Saitoum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the only difference is that the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Wever in De Wever, Sanfilippo, Riedel &amp; Gruber" authorityYear="1979" box="[151,232,619,645]" class="Polycystina" family="Poulpidae" genus="Poulpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nassellaria" pageId="18" pageNumber="23" phylum="Radiozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,232,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">Poulpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the three arches Al and AV marked as depressions on the surface of the cephalis, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pessagno" authorityYear="1977" box="[199,286,682,708]" class="Polycystina" family="Poulpidae" genus="Saitoum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nassellaria" pageId="18" pageNumber="23" phylum="Radiozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,286,682,708]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">Saitoum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has no arches.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,685,169,1669]" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">
In order to better understand the differences between the two genera we also examined some specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pessagno" authorityYear="1977" box="[267,351,778,804]" class="Polycystina" family="Poulpidae" genus="Saitoum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nassellaria" pageId="18" pageNumber="23" phylum="Radiozoa" rank="species" species="pagei">
<emphasis box="[267,280,778,804]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[297,351,778,803]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">pagei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from our material and found that this species has also the three arches Al and AV. They are very weak on some segments as compared to those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Wever in De Wever, Sanfilippo, Riedel &amp; Gruber" authorityYear="1979" box="[408,494,875,901]" class="Polycystina" family="Poulpidae" genus="Poulpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nassellaria" pageId="18" pageNumber="23" phylum="Radiozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[408,494,875,901]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">Poulpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and are marked externally by three longitudinal constrictions so that the cephalis of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pessagno" authorityYear="1977" box="[365,445,938,964]" class="Polycystina" family="Poulpidae" genus="Saitoum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nassellaria" pageId="18" pageNumber="23" phylum="Radiozoa" rank="species" species="pagei">
<emphasis box="[365,378,938,964]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[392,445,938,963]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">pagei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is three-lobate in apical view. 
<bibRefCitation author="TAKEMURA A." box="[259,461,971,997]" pageId="18" pageNumber="23" pagination="29 - 74" refId="ref35854" refString="TAKEMURA A. 1986. - Classification of Jurassic nassellarians (Radiolaria). Palaeontographica 195 A: 29 - 74." type="journal article" year="1986">Takemura (1986)</bibRefCitation>
showed also a well marked arch AV in 
<taxonomicName authority="De Wever, 1981" authorityName="De Wever" authorityYear="1981" class="Polycystina" family="Poulpidae" genus="Saitoum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nassellaria" pageId="18" pageNumber="23" phylum="Radiozoa" rank="species" species="levium">
<emphasis box="[380,552,1002,1029]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">Saitoum levium</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="DE WEVER P. &amp; CABY R." pageId="18" pageNumber="23" pagination="467 - 472" refId="ref34318" refString="DE WEVER P. &amp; CABY R. 1981. - Datation de la base des schistes lustres postophiolitiques par des radiolaires (Oxfordien superieur-Kimmeridgien moyen) dans les Alpes Cottiennes (Saint-Veran, France). Comptes Rendus de l'Academie des Sciences II, 292: 467 - 472." type="journal article" year="1981">De Wever, 1981</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Wever in De Wever, Sanfilippo, Riedel &amp; Gruber" authorityYear="1979" box="[344,428,1035,1061]" class="Polycystina" family="Poulpidae" genus="Poulpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nassellaria" pageId="18" pageNumber="23" phylum="Radiozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[344,428,1035,1061]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">Poulpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pessagno" authorityYear="1977" box="[364,451,1066,1092]" class="Polycystina" family="Poulpidae" genus="Saitoum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nassellaria" pageId="18" pageNumber="23" phylum="Radiozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[364,451,1066,1092]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">Saitoum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In order to preserve it we think that a better distinction between the two genera could be the presence or absence of the apical horn: the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Wever in De Wever, Sanfilippo, Riedel &amp; Gruber" authorityYear="1979" box="[445,526,1163,1189]" class="Polycystina" family="Poulpidae" genus="Poulpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nassellaria" pageId="18" pageNumber="23" phylum="Radiozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[445,526,1163,1189]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">Poulpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be characterized by the absence of the apical horn and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pessagno" authorityYear="1977" box="[151,239,1226,1252]" class="Polycystina" family="Poulpidae" genus="Saitoum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nassellaria" pageId="18" pageNumber="23" phylum="Radiozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,239,1226,1252]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">Saitoum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its presence. In all the three Triassic species initially assigned to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Wever in De Wever, Sanfilippo, Riedel &amp; Gruber" authorityYear="1979" box="[449,530,1259,1285]" class="Polycystina" family="Poulpidae" genus="Poulpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nassellaria" pageId="18" pageNumber="23" phylum="Radiozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[449,530,1259,1285]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">Poulpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[587,633,1258,1284]" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">type</typeStatus>
species included, the apical horn is absent. Other Triassic species assigned to this genus are also characterized by the absence of the apical horn, or when it is present it looks like a very short thorn. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pessagno" authorityYear="1977" box="[233,325,1418,1444]" class="Polycystina" family="Poulpidae" genus="Saitoum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nassellaria" pageId="18" pageNumber="23" phylum="Radiozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[233,325,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">Saitoum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, on the contrary, has always a rather well developed apical horn. A character common to both genera is also the absence of verticils of spines on feet.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,685,169,1669]" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pessagno" authorityYear="1977" box="[151,242,1546,1572]" class="Polycystina" family="Poulpidae" genus="Saitoum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nassellaria" pageId="18" pageNumber="23" phylum="Radiozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,242,1546,1572]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="23">Saitoum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described without a distal velum. Our well preserved material proves that a velum is almost always present, its absence being due to poor preservation.
</paragraph>
